<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-521-377  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 521 377.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Advanced Basic for PCs released. (Workstation Source's HT Basic3.0 for IBM-PCs) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Workstation Source (product introduction).andO;Product:   HTBasic 3.0 (Compiler) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionBASICProgramming LanguagesSoftware packagesSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ADVANCED BASIC FOR PCS RELEASED MAIDENHEAD, BERKSHIRE, 1990 SEP 3 (NB) --Workstation Source has released an advanced scientific and engineeringversion of Basic for IBM-compatible PCs.andP;  The package - HT Basic v3.0 - isclaimed to be fully compatible with Hewlett-Packard's HP Basic language -also known as Rocky Mountain Basic by aficionados - and runs in the normalDOS environment.andM;As with HP Basic, HT Basic supports a full screen editing and debuggingenvironment.andP;  The package has all the usual Basic syntax and languagecommands, as well as support for more than 40, device-independent, HPgraphics statements.andM;Interestingly, all the known bugs in HP Basic have been removed in HT Basic,according to Mark Lipscombe, Workstation Source's marketing manager.andM;&quot;In addition to providing full compatibility with HP Basic, HT Basic is apowerful scientific language in its own right,&quot; he said.andM;&quot;Basic has always provided an excellent environment for test and measurementapplications where frequent code changes are required.andP;  HT Basic adds thecomputational power and other facilities usually found in traditionalscientific languages like Fortran, Algol and APL,&quot; he added.andM;HT Basic is written in the C programming language and will run on any 286,386 or 486-based PC.andP;  Prices vary from UKP450 for a 286 version to UKP 1,000for a 386/486 version.andP;  These prices include an IEEE-488 card with full200/300 Series register-level compatibility.andM;(Steve Gold/19900830/Press andamp; Public Contact: Workstation Source - Tel:0628-75252)</TEXT></DOC>